"v. 篡改；说谎 【英】 v.窜改(to altera record, etc.fraudulently)；说谎(to tell falsehoods; lie) 【记】 fals(假)+ify→弄假 →窜改 【例】 The commander decided to falsify the report to trick the enemy. v. (通过增加或改变来)篡改 = forge; 说谎, 伪称(无根据地陈述) = lie = misrepresent 【记】false(adj 错误的; 假的; 伪造的; 人工的) 【参】falsification(n 弄虚作假; 伪造; 歪曲) 【记】fals 假 + ify使→弄假→窜改 falsify (v.)  mid-15c., ""to prove false,"" from Middle French falsifier (15c.), from Late Latin falsificare (see falsify). Meaning ""to make false"" is from c.1500. Earlier verb was simply falsen (c.1200). Related: Falsified; falsifying."
